-- Teresa Kerry Released From Hospital After Seizure Treatment
-- B y   A n n a   E d n e y
-- 2013-07-27T21:34:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-27/teresa-kerry-released-from-hospital-after-seizure-treatment.html
Teresa Heinz Kerry, the wife of
Secretary of State  John Kerry , was released today from the
 Boston  hospital where she was treated for a seizure she suffered
on July 7.  Kerry “walked out of Spaulding Rehabilitation Hospital in
Boston today after successful treatment for a seizure,” the
State Department said in an e-mailed statement. “Doctors said
they expect Mrs. Heinz Kerry to complete a full recovery at home
after some limited out-patient treatment.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anna Edney in Washington at 
 aedney@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mark Rohner at 
 mrohner@bloomberg.net  